hw-management (1.mlnx.7.0060.1048) unstable; urgency=low

  [ NVIDIA ]
  * bmc: isolate the MCTP iROT interface into a dedicated "mctp" network
    namespace so ifupdown2 (default netns) does not abort decoding the AF_MCTP
    (family 45) address; restores automatic eth0 DHCP on NVIDIA SONiC-BMC
    (Redmine #5016565). Adds hw-management-bmc-mctp-netns-isolate@.service plus
    the mctp-ns-exec helper, and reworks 99-hw-management-bmc-mctp.rules to
    trigger the service instead of configuring the EID in the default netns.
    On package (re)install the udev "add" event is re-fired for already-present
    mctpirot* devices so the fix applies without requiring a reboot.

